[2025-10-31 21:04:26] [OUTPUT] в•”в•җв•җв•җ рҹ“„ test_output.md (8.5 KB) в•җв•җв•җ\n# uDOS v1.1 - Human-Readable Core\n\n**uDOS** is an educational CLI framework that demonstrates how to build a modular, human-readable command system while integrating the Gemini API for AI-powered interactions.\n\nVersion 1.1 evolves uDOS from a proof-of-concept into a **production-ready CLI framework** with:\n- A **hybrid parser** that translates user-friendly commands into structured internal code (`uCODE`)\n- A **themed lexicon** system for customizable user experience\n- **Multi-panel text management** for organized data workflows\n- **Session logging** for complete interaction history\n- **Script execution** for automation and testing\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### 1. First-Time Setup\nWhen you first run uDOS, it will automatically guide you through a setup process:\n\n```bash\n./start_udos.sh\n```\n\nYou'll be prompted to enter:\n- Your name\n- Project/story name\n- Project description (optional)\n- Theme preference (DUNGEON_CRAWLER, CYBERPUNK, or MINIMAL)\n\nThis creates a `data/STORY.UDO` file that personalizes your uDOS experience.\n\n### 2. Environment Setup\n```bash\n# Activate the virtual environment (if not already activated)\nsource .venv/bin/activate\n\n# Ensure dependencies are installed\npip install -r requirements.txt\n\n# Add your Gemini API key to .env (for AI features)\necho 'GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here' > .env\n```\n\n### 3. Run uDOS\n```bash\n# Interactive mode (with smart completion!)\n./start_udos.sh\n\n# Run a script file (auto-creates default STORY.UDO if needed)\n./start_udos.sh shakedown.uscript\n```\n\n### 4. Interactive Features\nuDOS v1.1 includes a powerful interactive shell with:\n- **Smart Tab-Completion**: Press Tab for command suggestions with dropdown menus\n- **Context-Aware Completion**: Automatically suggests file paths for LOAD/SAVE/RUN, panel names for SHOW\n- **Auto-Suggest**: Previous commands appear as you type (press вҶ’ to accept)\n- **Command History**: Use вҶ‘/вҶ“ to navigate previous commands\n- **Dynamic Prompt**: Shows project name and active panel, e.g., `[my-quest] (main) uDUNGEON> `\n- **Smart Triggers**: Type `[` to instantly open command completion\n- **Personalized Experience**: Your name and project details from STORY.UDO\n\n### 5. VS Code Development\nPress `F5` to launch the debugger, or use the Command Palette (`Cmd+Shift+P`):\n- **Run Task** вҶ’ `Run uDOS Interactive`\n- **Run Task** вҶ’ `Run Shakedown Test`\n\n---\n\n## Core Architecture\n\nuDOS v1.1 uses a **hybrid architecture** that separates user-facing commands from internal execution:\n\n| Component | File | Purpose |\n|:----------|:-----|:--------|\n| **Main Loop** | `uDOS_main.py` | Entry point, handles interactive & script modes |\n| **Parser** | `uDOS_parser.py` | Translates user commands вҶ’ `uCODE` |\n| **Command Handler** | `uDOS_commands.py` | Executes `uCODE` instructions |\n| **Grid System** | `uDOS_grid.py` | Manages text panels for multi-buffer workflows |\n| **Session Logger** | `uDOS_logger.py` | Records all I/O to timestamped files in `sandbox/` |\n| **Commands Definition** | `data/COMMANDS.UDO` | JSON mapping of commands вҶ’ `uCODE` templates |\n| **Lexicon** | `data/LEXICON.UDO` | Themed terminology & messages |\n\n### uCODE Format\nAll commands are translated to a structured internal format:\n```\n[MODULE|COMMAND*PARAM1*PARAM2*...]\n```\n**Examples:**\n- `CATALOG` вҶ’ `[FILE|LIST*./*main]`\n- `LOAD "README.MD" TO "docs"` вҶ’ `[FILE|LOAD*README.MD*docs]`\n- `ASK "What is uDOS?"` вҶ’ `[AI|ASK*What is uDOS?*null]`\n\n---\n\n## Available Commands\n\n| Command | Syntax | Description |\n|:--------|:-------|:------------|\n| **CATALOG** | `CATALOG ["<path>"]` | List directory contents |\n| **LOAD** | `LOAD "<file>" [TO "<panel>"]` | Load file into panel |\n| **SAVE** | `SAVE "<panel>" TO "<file>"` | Save panel to file |\n| **GRID PANEL CREATE** | `GRID PANEL CREATE "<name>"` | Create new text panel |\n| **GRID PANELS LIST** | `GRID PANELS LIST` | Show all panels |\n| **SHOW** | `SHOW "<panel>"` | Display panel contents |\n| **ASK** | `ASK "<question>" [FROM "<panel>"]` | Query Gemini AI |\n| **RUN** | `RUN "<script>"` | Execute uDOS script file |\n| **HELP** | `HELP [<command>]` | Show command help |\n| **CLS** | `CLS` | Clear screen |\n\n---\n\n## Development Workflow\n\n### Dev Round Process\n1. **Plan** вҶ’ Update `ROADMAP.MD` with phase goals\n2. **Implement** вҶ’ Create/modify Python modules\n3. **Test** вҶ’ Run `./start_udos.sh shakedown.uscript`\n4. **Debug** вҶ’ Use VS Code debugger (`F5`) or add breakpoints\n5. **Validate** вҶ’ Review session logs in `sandbox/session_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.log`\n6. **Commit** вҶ’ Git commit with clear message\n\n### Testing Strategy\n- **Shakedown Test**: `shakedown.uscript` validates all core features\n- **Interactive Testing**: Launch uDOS and manually test commands\n- **Session Logs**: Check `sandbox/` for complete I/O history\n\n### VS Code Integration\n- **Settings**: `.vscode/settings.json` configures Python environment\n- **Launch Configs**: `.vscode/launch.json` provides debug profiles\n- **Tasks**: `.vscode/tasks.json` defines build/test tasks\n\n### Debugging Tips\n- Set breakpoints in `uDOS_parser.py` to inspect command parsing\n- Set breakpoints in `uDOS_commands.py` to inspect uCODE execution\n- Use the **uDOS: Run Shakedown Script** launch config to debug test runs\n- Check `sandbox/logs/session_*.log` for full interaction history\n- Review `data/STORY.UDO` for your session metadata and preferences\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nuDOS/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ uDOS_main.py          # Main application & run loop\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ uDOS_parser.py        # Command parser (user input вҶ’ uCODE)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ uDOS_commands.py      # Command handlers (uCODE вҶ’ actions)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ uDOS_grid.py          # Multi-panel text management\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ uDOS_logger.py        # Session logging system\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ uDOS_splash.py        # ASCII art banner\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ uDOS_completer.py     # Smart context-aware completion\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ uDOS_setup.py         # First-time setup & STORY.UDO management\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ start_udos.sh         # Launch script (activates venv)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ shakedown.uscript     # Automated test script\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ data/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ COMMANDS.UDO      # Command definitions (JSON)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ LEXICON.UDO       # Themed terminology (JSON)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ STORY.UDO         # User/project data (auto-created, gitignored)\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ STORY.UDO.template # Template for STORY.UDO\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ sandbox/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ logs/             # Session logs (timestamped)\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ ...               # Temp files, script outputs\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ knowledge/            # User documentation & stories\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ .vscode/              # VS Code workspace config\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ .venv/                # Python virtual environment\nв””в”Җв”Җ README.MD             # This file\n```\n\n---\n\n## Customization\n\n### Add a New Command\n1. **Define** in `data/COMMANDS.UDO`:\n```json\n{\n  "NAME": "MYCOMMAND",\n  "SYNTAX": "MYCOMMAND \"<param>\"",\n  "DESCRIPTION": "Does something cool",\n  "UCODE_TEMPLATE": "[SYSTEM|MYCOMMAND*$1]",\n  "DEFAULT_PARAMS": {}\n}\n```\n\n2. **Implement** handler in `uDOS_commands.py`:\n```python\ndef handle_system_command(self, command, params, grid, parser):\n    # ...existing code...\n    elif command == "MYCOMMAND":\n        return self.get_message("ACTION_SUCCESS", action=params[0])\n```\n\n3. **Add lexicon entries** in `data/LEXICON.UDO` (optional themed names)\n\n### Customize Theme\nEdit `data/LEXICON.UDO` to change prompt style, command aliases, and all user-facing messages.\n\n---\n\n## Current Status (v1.1)\n\nвң… **Completed:**\n- Hybrid parser with multi-word command support\n- Session logging with timestamped files\n- Grid system for multi-panel text management\n- Script execution engine\n- Comprehensive lexicon system\n- VS Code development environment\n- **Interactive shell with `prompt_toolkit`**\n- **Smart context-aware completion**\n- **Dynamic prompt with panel indicators**\n- **Auto-suggest from command history**\n\nрҹҺү **Phase 6 Complete:**\n- All interactive shell enhancements implemented\n- Context-aware file path and panel name completion\n- Smart key bindings for enhanced UX\n- Complete-while-typing support\n\nрҹ“Ӣ **Roadmap:**\nSee `ROADMAP.MD` for full development plan\n\n---\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\nThis project demonstrates:\n- **Modular Architecture**: Separation of concerns (parsing, execution, UI)\n- **Data-Driven Design**: Commands and terminology defined in JSON\n- **Hybrid Systems**: Human-readable layer over structured backend\n- **API Integration**: Gemini AI integration patterns\n- **Testing Strategies**: Automated script-based testing\n- **Development Tooling**: VS Code workspace configuration\n\n---\n\n## Contributing\n\nSee `CONTRIBUTING.md` and `STYLE-GUIDE.MD` for contribution guidelines.\n\n---\n\n## License\n\nEducational project - see repository for license details.\n\n\nв•ҡв•җв•җв•җ End of test_output.md в•җв•җв•җ\n
